SPORTS fans using North Ayrshire Athletics Club now have a new shelter thanks to a Commonwealth Games legacy fund. Games boost will shelter local athletes SPORTS fans using North Ayrshire Athletics Club now have a new shelter thanks to a Commonwealth Games legacy fund.The shelter is an extension of the club's vision to be a centre for sporting excellence.Club chairman Blair Pettigrew said the shelter was a &quot;shot in the arm&quot; and provided a much needed multi-use facility to enhance its sporting efforts.Councillor Alan Hill, Commonwealth Champion and Cabinet Member for Community, Culture and Policy, said: &quot;This new addition to NAAC is a sure sign that the North Ayrshire Legacy Plan is right on track in delivering legacy outcomes.&quot;It will provide an essential gathering point for athletes.&quot; 